cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the characterization of handover rates in ultra-dense networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses tools from stochastic geometry, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper studies the impact of user height on the association and handover rate, which can be related to the category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the need for balancing the handover load among the network tiers, which can be related to the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper may also be related to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia), as it deals with the support of diverse devices in ultra-dense networks.
